    "chemicalDescription": [
      "sr-(Methionyl Hexapeptide-40 Oligopeptide-231 s-Spider Polypeptide-1) Formate is a single chain recombinant peptide, produced by fermentation in E. coli. The starting gene is synthesized by the fusion of the gene from s-Spider Polypeptide-1, Oligopeptide-231, and Hexapeptide-40 with the initiation code for methionine. The fusion peptide is esterified with formic acid and contains 1190 amino acids which may contain disulfide bonds and/or glycosylation and consists of the proper sequence of the 20 standard amino acids."
    ],
